- Delete the data off one replica and restart it, so it's in initial sync (in state startup2)
- run the program below that attempts to delete a non-existant user repeatedly.
- run "netstat --inet -n" on either the client or the server and watch as you build up open idle sockets. Note further that you only build up idle sockets to the machine that is syncing, not other secondaries or the primary.
